      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MINTER POWER (7) turned in a better effort at Sale last start, finishing third behind Paw Irulan (24.87) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Expected to feature in the finish again. CHARLIE'S ROSE (4) was never in contention last time at Warragul, but prior to that won by a neck at Warragul (22.80) beating Extremity in a Grade 7 on February 13. The form out of her last race has been franked. Should be in this for a long way. PLATOON (1) is progressing well claiming his 2nd career win latest, scoring by 2.75 lengths (17.49) at Mt Gambier. Winner at his latest appearance in the quickest time on the card. Can measure up again. ABSOLUTE RUPEE (2) missed the frame latest (31.18) when sixth over 525m at The Meadows in a Grade 5. Has already won two times from this draw.",
